\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Your name is James Sullivan, what is your address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 38 Kelso Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 You're }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2979009 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827  aren't you?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 When did you get }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2979009 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 1926. Actually the first day of the general strike. May the third.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 When were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 When?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Where?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 I was born in a little street off Bowarth Street. In 1904 - March.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How many years did you live in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 I lived in that house 'til I was twenty-two. 'Til I got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2979009 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 So that was the only house you lived in all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 One brother, two sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Would you give me their birth order please.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Sister 1902. Another sister in 1906 and a brother at 1908.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How old was your father when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 About twenty-five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Cork - Ireland.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What was his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 He was a building labourer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did he have another job before or after he became a building labourer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well he worked at the Liverpool Docks during the first world war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 All I want to talk about is up to 1918 really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 I see, well he was in the docks during the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did he have any casual or part time jobs after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What did he do until his death?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well he was retired when he was about seventy. He died at eighty-five. Prior to that he was working 
in - down South in London area in the building.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Where was he working in Liverpool?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 He worked in a - what they - in the old days called the Gerry builders. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What's the Gerry builders?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well the Gerry builders where they used to throw up the houses by - you know, one in a week - shoddy work and all - this kind of thing.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What kind of houses were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 The workers houses, yes, small terraced houses, yes, four rooms and - no bath, no inside toilet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Do you ever remember your father being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Yes. I remember him out of work when I was in the infants school. He was out of work every time there was frost or snow, the building trades were out of work, they didn't get any dole or anything like that in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How old was your mother when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Twenty-one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well she was born in New York.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Do you know if she had any jobs before she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2979009 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes, she was in service - in service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did she work after she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2979009 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No, she never worked after she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2979009 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did she have any part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How many rooms were there in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Four. Two down, two up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 There were no reception rooms then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No reception rooms, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did anyone else besides your parents and brother and sisters live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No. Just us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No relatives or lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No relatives or lodgers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No. Good God no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Was the washing done at home or was it sent out?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well that is ridiculous question.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did your mother or father mend or make the families clothing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes, me father used to mend the boots. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Were the clothes new or second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10188749\charrsid483827  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 hand that you bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well they were usually new but they were on cheques.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Perhaps you'd explain what a cheque is?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well a cheque is that you - received a chit for a certain amount of money and then - somebody collected each week a tanner or a
 shilling in the pound until it was paid for, you always had to pay a bit of interest on it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 And your dad always repaired the shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Cooking, washing up, cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
No. As a matter of fact he wasn't able to. At that time he - his work might take him from here to Garston, he didn't have enough money for car fare. He'd have to walk and he'd finish at night and have to walk home after carrying a
 hod all day up and down ladders - he wouldn't be fit to do any - all he was fit was to nod in a chair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did he dress or undress or bath you or read to you or tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well he told us plenty of stories, usually pretty good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Would he take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh yes, yes, he would take me out, he'd take me round the park and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did he look after you when she was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Usually, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you have any jobs you had to carry out regularly at home to help your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No. But I had jobs outside home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 You didn't have to do any jobs at all in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Not in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 I used to have to cut the Echo up for toilet paper - any jobs like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well - yes, there was little - they
 were chores but not jobs. Chores, yes, there was little chores like that. My father used to breed canary - he had a shed in the back yard, he bred canaries as a hobby. And as money making hobby of course. I used to have to help to clear out there and - s
ee, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did your brothers and sisters have any regular jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No, not - I wouldn't say they had regular jobs in the home, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did the older children help the younger children with things they found difficult such as dressing or eating or look after them in any way?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Well they looked after them - they more or less had to, I mean that was the - the kind of creed they had in those days. The younger were always looked after by the elders.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did the younger children help the older ones in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Not much, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 At what age did you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh very early age - very, v
ery early age. More self - well you were self - sufficient at very early age at that time. I - I could put myself to bed at six seven or eight easily.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you share the bedroom or bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes. Had to share the bed with - my brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What was the seeping arrangements of the whole family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Well the sleeping arrangement of the whole family was that there was two beds in one room, one in the other and the two girls slept in one room and the two boys had to - be in the same bedroom with the mother and father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What room did you have a bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 None.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 When did you bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh well, every - every weekend, it'd be in front of the fire in a tub.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 In the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 In the kitchen, yes. In an old barrel cut down into a tub. Oh yes, the old man made that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 When did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Each week. Each week, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 In the - one - living room - kitchen as it was called.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 That would be the back kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No, the kitchen. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Were there occasions when you ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh we might in the back kitchen if there was - visitors in the other room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Where did your mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 In the back kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did she have a gas cooker?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No - fire. Oven. Fire and oven, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
When was breakfast eaten - on an ordinary day what members of the family were present and did your dad have his breakfast beforehand or did he take it out with him or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well he took it out
 with him because he started work at six o'clock in the mornings in those days and he had breakfast on the job. We didn't see him 'til he came home at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What happened to breakfast for the rest of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well we had it going - before going to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 All of you at the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Usually, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What did you usually have to eat and drink for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 For breakfast? Bread and jam. Bread and dripping - something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What did you have to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you have anything different on certain days - such as Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh yes, Sunday of course you'd be - Sunday morning breakfast might have a bit of salt fish or bit of bacon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Dinner of course you'd get as roast dinner - we always had ro
ast dinner on Sunday. But usually in the week your dinner was in the evening when the old man came home. And - and then you'd have of course the steak or liver - bacon and egg. There'd always be potatoes - potatoes was a great thing with every - dinner.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 And the evening meal on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Well evening meal on a Sunday would be in the form of just a tea. Mother usually baked cakes or pies or something Sunday afternoon. Usually have them Sunday evening for your tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did your mother bake her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Occasionally - not always but she did pretty regularly, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did she make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No, not fruit or that - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did she make any medicine or wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well made medicines - the great thing was seenna tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What was senna tea?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Senna tea - you bought senna leaves from the chemist and then they used to stew them and make a kind of a tea out of them and - this was given round at - once a week to all members of the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What was it for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 It was - for the bowels.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Just like li}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81131\charrsid483827 qu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
orice powder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 That's correct. Yes, it was senna tea. And - in the spring time used to have a great - fettish for giving you sulphur and treacle. That 
was - to clear the blood they thought at that time, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Was there any beer brewed in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did your father or mother grow their on vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No, no, there was only a back yard, nothing to grow - grow any stuff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you buy any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Buy - yes we did buy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Tinned or dried?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh no, fresh usually - there was very little tinned. Very little tinned stuff used in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did they keep any livestock for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Occasionally hens, yes, just before Christmas probably he'd - kill hen or two and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Who looked after the hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well we did usually. We - the children, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh well - four or five times in a week, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Was it tinned meat or fresh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No, no, no, no. Well it was stews, scouces and things like that. Fourpenn'rth of mutton pieces and - that'd make a scouse. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Fourpenn'orth or twopenn'orth of pieces or half a pound of neck of mutton or half a pound of scrag end?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
That's correct. Yes, that was the kind of stuff we had. Yes, well I mean, you'd go - I've gone and you get fourpenn'orth of mutton pieces which was a pound - one pound weight and you'd get five pound of potatoes for about - threeha'pence. Yo
u'd get ha'porth of pot herbs. And - these were mixed herbs that go in the - and than'd make a pot of scouse, yes, for a family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 And maybe last more than one day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes, probably.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you ever get some extra meat such as rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
No, we didn't get it from poaching but we did get rabbit, I mean rabbits were reasonably cheap in those days. You'd get a rabbit for sixpence or seven}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81131\charrsid483827  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 pence. And it did make a meal for a family a rabbit, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Do you remember ever seeing your mother having less food so the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Yes. I - I can honestly say that, yes, that she had deprived herself occasionally when things had been tight - when - quite obviously this was so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did your father have more food than the rest of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well, no, he - no. The same thing you say would apply to him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Were you allowed to talk during the meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No. In fact if you weren't allowed to talk, you were told - wasn't allowed during eating, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 You were made to eat what was cooked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What was your parents attitude if you left some food uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Very - their attitude was very hostile. It'd be forced on you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
If there was something on the table you wanted like the salt could you ask someone to pass it to you or did you have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No, you could ask someone to pass it to you, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well you could but it wouldn't often be there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way and sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well - you had to sit upright but I don't think there was ever anything about th
e way you held your knife and fork. They were very keen that you ate properly. Oh yes. We were made to eat properly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh when you were told. Not until you were told, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did all the family sit at the table for the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Usually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you always have the same places at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes. Yes, that's -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How was the meal served and by whom? Was it served in tureens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh no. No, no. Served all on the plates and your mother served it usually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What order would she serve in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well me father usually got his first and then I don't think there was any particular order afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Where did the younger brothers and sisters sit before they could feed themselves?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well they usually sat on the - an old sofa that was there - there was no special place for them really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Who fed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well as far as I can remember - while I can remember they could always feed themsel
ves bar one that was the baby I mean. I mean it's a - I don't think it's anything I could say about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 When were they able to join family meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 From a very early age. Very early age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well - no, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did she show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 If you had any worries could you share them with her or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well, no - I'd say no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Was your father an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did he show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well rarely - he was brusque - more brusque. He - he didn't like to show it - I think he had it but he didn't like to show it you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 If you had any worries could you share them with him or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well no, you didn't do because he was a bit unapproachable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well they - expected you to be very servile to them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Could you say what way that would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Well the way would be that you had to treat them as much as you treat yourself - that they had to be considered part of - your family - family unit - yes, unit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did they say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes. Fight your own battles was a great saying.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 I think they - expected, particularly mother, expected us to be - a little bit snobbish, a little but above your class. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did your parents bring you up to consider certain things in life important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Oh yes. Yes. Well I - I think the most important thing the old man used to touch on was honesty and truthfulness. They wanted you always to speak the truth.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well me father did swear, me mother never swore - I never heard me mother swear. And of course we never swore in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No. Definitely no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 If you did something your parents didn't like you doing what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well we would - we're in for a hiding. Hidings were given out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Who used to do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 The old - father usually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How often did you get a hiding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Oh I daresay two or three times a week. It was saved up for you, if you did anything during the day your mother of course'd say, wait you're your father comes in, and he would be duly informed and you'd be c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8002936\charrsid483827 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8002936\charrsid483827 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 tised.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Do you remember any particular occasion when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 There's one or two occasions that I was punished and I didn't deserve to be - that stands out in me mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How did you feel about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well I was, resented it - still do amazingly. I - I - I've got an a
wful sense of justice even apart from myself against - with others and injustice I hate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 I should think it's even more so when it's applied to yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 It is, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Would you say you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents or did one play a more important part that the other?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
I think the mother played a more important part - I think my mother played more important part from the way - behaviour. I think she had more to do with us in that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Because the father in those days had to spend so much time at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Time away from the home. And when he did }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8002936\charrsid483827 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 et home he was usually too tired to - take part in any of the home activities.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Would be a shade different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you get any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 You - you usually got a small present or - token or card of some kind. It was an event in your life a birthday, yes.
