\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Do you know what party he voted for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well he voted for Liberal before there was a Labour candidate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 In some places at that time men felt they risked losing their job or their house if they voted differently from their e
mployers - do you know if your father felt himself under that kind of pressure to vote for a particular political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No, never at any time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 But do you think it was right that there was a risk of losing his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 I - I - I don't think he would think of that at all - he - he'd vote according to his principles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 But it's quite possible he could lose his job had he done so do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Quite possible I suppose but - his - his job was always a terrible job anyhow. The building was never constant job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Was your father a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Not that I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Do you remember him working for one during an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh - no, I don't think he did, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Was your mother a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did your parents take part in any political activity other than at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No. Industrial politics but not ; Parliamentary politics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Perhaps you'd be able to explain that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well he took active part in union, you see. Yes. He was - he was President of a branch of the Altogether, in fact he was in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 The Altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes, the Altogether was a - a building labourers union.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 That would be a union for unskilled men?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Unskilled building workers. At that time - u
p to that time there was no organisation for the - labourers. The craft unions - the plasterers and the brick-layers had a section for them but - obviously they were always kept down so this Altogether was started to bring all the - unskilled labour of th
e building - together.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 And your dad took an interest in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh yes, he was active - very active part in that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well usually - reading I suppose - the papers, the newspaper or - sleeping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did your mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No, she'd not time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh yes, they'd go out - pictures during the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Who would she go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh she'd generally go with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8002936\charrsid483827 m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 e sister - me eldest sister or perhaps the old man occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 When did your father get home from work in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Usually six to half past.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How many evenings a week would he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh all. He didn't go out much. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did your father attend any clubs or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 He didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 So your mother didn't attend any either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No. We}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8002936\charrsid483827 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
l - there wasn't any money for that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did your father take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No. No, none at all, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did he attend the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did he bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 You did mention about your father's method of gambling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well of course he would have an odd bet with what he could do physically himself. Well he
 - on the job he'd - he'd take a bag of cement under each arm and he'd run a hundred yards with it for a bet or he'd jump on a bike and carry a bucket of water with his arm outstretched for so far. These - these kind of physical efforts he'd - he'd have a
 little bet on. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did your father and mother belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Yes, they belonged to a penny savings bank run by the Norwood Mission, Bowlers Street. It was a little penny bank. Yes, it was run by this mission hall, it was - quite a
 few of them were knocking about in those years, do you remember them? Penny banks, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 There were a lot of tontines too weren't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh yes, there were tontines, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Was he member of any sick club or funeral club or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 We
ll of course the only funeral club in be a member of would be a little - penny policy with some insurance probably but - no, I don't think they were in any sick club, no. He was usually in such rude health you know that I don't think it ever crossed his m
ind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Well - we didn't mix as regards outside efforts - we didn't knock about together. We had our other interests. We had our own friends, our own interests outside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 My father used to say you select your friends but your relatives are thrust upon you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Thrust upon you, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Was there one of your brothers or sisters that you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Not overwhelmingly no. No - I - I think we were all fairly close but not so - in the extent of knocking about together outside of the home.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 As a child who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 I usually played with one or two lads around the neighbourhood that - were born round the same time as me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Not your brothers or sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Where did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 In the streets mostly, round the back entry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you ever play in anybody's home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No. No, there was no room for that kind of thing you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well there was - ollies - t
hree holes. There was kick the can. There was - really-o. Any kind of thing - or peggy and buttons. Buttons - cost no money that was the thing - the games you played cost no money - they didn't have any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Well we - we say this, we got dirty and we got told off about it - getting your boots - your toecaps scuffed climbing walls and this kind of thing you'd - you would get told off about it or you would get chastised for it but it didn't stop you doing 
it - it was never - put into you in a fearsome way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did your parents discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you belong to any youth organisations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 There were none.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you have any hobbies when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No, I had no hobbies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you keep any pets, collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 There was nothing - nowhere to keep pets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you collect cigarette cards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh yes, we might collect cigarette cards or - yes you would - or cherry stones. Cherry wabs as we call them. They had a certain value.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you go fishing - for walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No. No, didn't go fishing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 For walks or cycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 I went cycling - I got an old bike for 
twelve and six - old second hand bike, I know I saved up long enough and I got it for twelve and six. Oh and I done quite a lot of biking in those days that way. Of course the country was pretty near.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Who did you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh three or four mates.
 One of them became a cycling champion of Liverpool - Larry Ross. Larry Ross - we did and he had an old bike costing about ten bob his first bike.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Larry Ross is over sixty now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Larry Ross is my age - sixty-five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Larry Ross has entered for the veteran races now hasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 I didn't know that. He lived in Mansell Road here off Alder Street - yes - Larry Ross.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 I used to do an awful lot of cycling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you. Well Larry was one - was one of our party in those days. We'd go out to S
immons Wood of a Sunday 'cos that was all - country them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Only - football. We - we had a little football club - Eversley which incidentally they made me chairman. I don't know why. And - we played friendly matches mostly, we weren't in any league - played friendly match down on Lister Drive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Where the allotments used to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you go to any theatres or concerts or music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Or cinemas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Not at school, no, I did after I left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How much was it - was it regularly?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 When I was a child at school, one half penny on a Saturday. A Saturday half penny we called it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What did you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well usually on kali suckers or everlasting strip, something that - get quite a lot for a ha'penny. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after her house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Only when she was ill - if she was ill or - during a confinement the neighbours'd generally come in and give a hand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Or relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well, no, wasn't any relatives around. Neighbours, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How would they do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh well, they just come in and take over and that was it, I mean, that was the type of
 thing you had in those days. If people were in trouble their neighbours usually just walked in and took charge. That's the way it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Four roomed houses lent themselves to that didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 That's right. It was a little cul-de-sc - was only fo
urteen houses in this cul-de-sac. It was a little community on it's own. Ah well - of course this - you don't know people here you see, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 You said the neighbours came in if your mother was ill or confined to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Not very near, no, there was one aunt I had, she lived off Kensington.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How much did you see of them - did you see much of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No. You'd see them about two or three times a year. You might visit you on a Sunday evening - there'd be a - a bit of an event.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 They'd come and see you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes, or you'd go and see - my mother and father'd go and see them. Be an event - anybody visiting really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did your parents have any friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Not - real - close friends, no. Acquaintances more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did they share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well, yes, what friends they had, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Where did they see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 They didn't you see, they were only like acquaintances. They didn't visit any friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did your mother have friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No. Only neighbours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Where did she see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Over the garden - over the back yard wall. Yes. At the back entry-leaning on the brush.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did your father have friends of his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well he had his - union blokes that came round Sunday mornings usually - discussing various - union matters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 They came round to your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes. Sunday morning usually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Sort of meeting would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Was this a regular thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh usual, yes, go on for - yes, pretty regular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Were friends ever invited to your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Except these people that came round for meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 That's all, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Were they ever offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 On any particular days or occasions would they come round - the only people who came round were the friends or your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Usually, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Would you say that the friends invited in were your mother's friends or your father's friends or were they friends of both of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 I'd say they were father's - wouldn't say friends - colleagues more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did friends call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did neighbours call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No, not reall
y. You were only there - strange thing about this you know - only when they were wanted. You wouldn't see a lot of neighbours until something happened - a sickness, illness and then they'd be there. That was the kind of thing that was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 People often t
ell us in those days they had to make their own amusements - what do you think your parents did when they got together with their friends and neighbours - did they have music or games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well I'll tell you what was a - a big thing you know that came ou
t in those days was the phonograph. The phonograph came out - not the gramophone, it preceded the gramophone. It was a phonograph with the round cylinder - wax cylinders you know. And these were a great thing when they first came. Somebody'd buy one and t
he door'd he left open and the neighbours'd be listening to it and - my father, his great favourite was John McCormick. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Many people divide society into different social classes or groups, in that time before 1818 did you think of some peop
le belonging to one and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Can you tell me what the different ones were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Well - to my mind as I can recall it you know I lived in a neighbourhood where there was - the houses had no bathrooms, no inside toilets and I co
uld go along the road to the top to where there was houses built with these and sitting rooms. I thought they were a class apart from me. I thought they were a higher class than I was. And further along when I got along the Sheer Road had the people that 
had the servants you know. I thought they were another class - higher again. I thought they were in tiers these classes see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What class or group would you say you belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 The working class - quite definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What sort of people belonged to the same class as you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Well they were really what they used to call in them days the artisan class. They - they had a little bit better type of living - of course they got a lot higher wages - I mean tradesmen like engineers and joiners were
 - were on about two guineas a week. Whereas the labouring classes were eighteen, nineteen and twenty shilling a week which is considerably lower. I mean if you take pro rata to the values I mean they were only on fifty per cent of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What kind of group would you say you belonged to at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 I belonged to the labouring class group which was the lowest group.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What sort of people belonged to the other classes or groups you mentioned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well they were the - there trades people - the
 tradesmen as they were known as, tradesmen as distinct from trades people - shopkeepers and that. Tradesmen - like engineers and joiners. They - they were a - a different class in those days. And they considered themselves a different class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Any other group that you can remember - the people who didn't work in industry - what about office workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Ah well of course they had a clerk class as we call them then - a clerk class. They were very superior in their way but they weren't considerably bett
er off than us. In - in fact, they weren't as well off as the tradesmen were. Although they - they'd have bigger ideas than - they weren't considerably well off at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently to people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Were you ever taught to touch your cap or show respect in some way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 I was always taught to show respect but not to touch me cap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 To whom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well to - older people than myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Was there anyone you called sir or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 In school it would be different wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh yes. But - you would call the schoolmaster sir but - we didn't call the teachers - lady teachers madam, we called 'em Miss. Miss.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 In the district where you lived who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well I think the shopkeepers. I think so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you come in contact with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well yes, usually - don
e the errands you know. Great thing in those days were the children did run the errands and of course most of the errands were on tick. You took a book and you had your book marked what you'd got then you - you paid at the end of the week. Everything was 
on tick. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Why do you reckon they were considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Well because - they provided the tick whereby you lived. This is the kind of thing you see it was and I mean even the clothes you wore - were on tick - they were on credit - nothing bought for cash.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Who did the shopkeepers associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Well the shopkeepers themselves normally I think associated with shopkeepers. There - they - they seemed to keep to themselves the trades people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Who did the clergy mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well of course they always mixed with the better off people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 And the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 They always mixed with the better off people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you have any contact with employers in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No, not really. Had occasion - there were occasions when the employers would come to see my father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What sort of people would you say went to the church and to the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Chapel was the non-conformist. Yes, well I - I say this that - the majority that attended churches were of the artisan class. Yes
, I - I wouldn't say that - the labouring classes so much as the artisan and trades}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8002936\charrsid483827  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 people - shopkeepers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Who would attend the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well I think they - they were mostly the same weren't they. Got a lot of Welsh people in this town - that - th
at attended those places and a lot of them were joiners you know - and craftsmen - building - yes, they were, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Where you lived did all the people in your group have the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups amongst t
hat section?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No, I think the standard of living was more or less - on the one level - very low. I don't think it could have got much lower.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Could you describe a family within the group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Such as the - their conditions? Well here's the point
 - every family that I knew used the pawn shop. They had to pawn clothes and articles in the week and then they - they pledge them in the week and then they get them out on the Saturday - the weekend. Then they go back in again Monday morning. This was so
mething that the whole neighbourhood did. Which was a proof of the level of the - living I mean, this was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 A tradesman would be above that wouldn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes. Yes. The tradesman would be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Do you think that one group felt itself superior to the rest.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Yes, the tradesman group very much so in those days. There was a tremendous barrier between the two. The craftsman and the non-craftsman. That's - that's been a lot - well, eliminated a lot now but in those days it carried an awful lot of 
weight if you was a tradesman and the trouble was that the like of my parents, along with a lot of others, the one thing was that when we left school we had to have a trade. That was a thing that was in their minds at all time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Do you remember a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes. Quite so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes or groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
I think so - I don't think that they mixed sufficiently to let it make a difference if you understand me. The only met people as acquaintances - they didn't have any real close friends. People didn't in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class or group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 I think she did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Can you tell me why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well I think she always - felt that she was a bit superior to the type of people she was living around. Her background - her backgr
ound from service, I think helped that a lot you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Even though she came ....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Yes, I still think this service background - being in service had this but she - she always tried even though she'd go into debt to cheque to try and make - dress 
you a little bit better. As a matter of fact, my sister won a scholarship at school and - there was a from to fill in, she had to go to the poli - to the Notre Dame College she was going to Eveton Valley, and there was a from to fill in and when it was fi
l
led in and went back there was a sister in charge of the girls school, she sent for my mother and - it was during the first world war and she put on it dock labourer - father was a dock labourer. The Sister sent for my mother and said she didn't believe i
t
. That her children didn't look like dock labourers children. True. And - she thought it wouldn't be right to let her go to this school and have on that form dock labourer. And she got her to change it to stevedore. Sister did that, yes. That's right, yes
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Was it possible at that time to move from one group to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No, it wasn't easy because they - they didn't want the lower stratas joint the upper ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 So you can't remember anybody who did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Oh yes. But this real gentleman, real lady had been applicable even to the lower strata. It hasn't been by virtue of their position. They have been called a thorough gentleman and a thorough lady even apart from their social standing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Because they'd earned it in their - in the way they were. I mean - its surprising you know even amongst this class you found people that were perfect gentlemen - perfect ladies. I found them myself.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 By their actions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes. The way they lived - their attitudes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 By their action to other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Do you remember seeing a policeman round where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh good gracious, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well
 they were - very down to earth. If they seen you doing anything that you shouldn't be doing it'd be a clip behind the ear or a kick up the backside or - and that kind of thing. But we weren't - we didn't - look up policemen with fear. No. We respected th
em a lot. We'd respect them more than fear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 When you were naughty did your mother ever say, I'll call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How do you think the policemen treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well I thing they treated them reasonably well. 'Cos I'm a
 little bit biased because I believe that after the 1919 strike we lost the best police}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3292730\charrsid483827  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
force. How the bobbies treated the policemen - you mean how the police treated the public, is that what you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How the police treated the public, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Wel
l - there was a - quite a good feeling between the police and the public as I pointed out before, it might be on the other end, but I think we lost a good police}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3292730\charrsid483827  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 force when that strike was on. We - you see, the type of policeman you got in those days were 
recruited from the working classes you see. You didn't get what you got later on in the twenties you got these college type police.; Trenchard's policemen you know, they were - they were - they made the examination that way that you had to be like matricu
lation and all this kind of thing with the what the equivalent of the present day 0 levels I suppose. That was the type of thing you had to have to be a policeman. Where prior to that, no, they were more practical types. They were good types.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you see much of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Very good landlord }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3292730\charrsid483827 we had. He - this little cul-de-}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 sac of - street of houses was pride and joy, come round and he'd even check latches o
n the back door himself. And he'd see they were replaced, he - the houses were painted every five years outside. And the old man used to - do his inside decorating pretty regularly and he would always allow - if he done a room he would always allow a week
s rent. He would. Very good type. He was a Welshman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Do you remember feeling that your parents had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh I know they had a struggle to make ends meet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What did you think about that at that time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 I was - well - it - it helped to make me a rebel say. Against society.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What difference did it make to the family when your father was ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well it made a lot of difference - there was no money coming in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How often was he ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Very seldom, he was very robust and he worked - and he always worked for the highest rate of pay he could get. Even if it was harder work.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you ever get help from the Guardians or the Parish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No. Well of course in those days don't forget go to the parish wasn't like going to Social Security now. Go}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3292730\charrsid483827  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
to a place, Brown Terrace, and all they'd issue you there would be a long loaf and a few - bits of margarine and things like that. There was no such thing as giving you any money. And it w
as considered degrading by the people of those time. Even the people that were really in need of it, they considered it degrading.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 If there was someone in the district that the people - might disapprove of very strongly was there any special way in wh
ich they showed it? Such as an effigy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh good God, no. No, nothing like that. In fact I can't recollect anybody in ; the neighbourhood that would - people took exception to.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 When you first started what time in the morning did you go and when did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Nine o'clock in the morning, home at dinner time - twelve o'clock, back at half past one. Finish at four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What kind of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh a church school - church - R.C. school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How did you get to - school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Walked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Who took you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Took yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Somebody must have took you at first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh well, your mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How long did it take you to get there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh only about five minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you come home for your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Came home, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 And you had the usual menu you were telling me about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What did you have for your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well you'd only have a - bit of bread and cheese or - something lik
e that. It wouldn't be a cooked meal. It would only be just bread and - dripping and things like - it was nothing cooked 'til night.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 I liked school. I liked it. I'm not saying they liked me a lot in lots of cases but - I - I done fairly well at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Well I got on - the teachers I got up against occasionally. 'Cos I was - the trouble with me was that I was at school during the war a lot. Big years. I mean I left scho
ol at the end of '17. 1917. Now - I don't know - I did get through school pretty good, I finished up in ex seven pretty early and then I was used for teaching the lower classes. I - I taught standard two for quite a long while afterwards - to take the dif
ferent young classes. I was - supervised by the headmaster but - that's the kind of thing I did, I spent the last eighteen months I was at school doing that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did your teachers emphasise certain things as important in life - manners, tidiness, punctuality or ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
No. We had very big classes and - were quite a lot of rough and ready types went to this school - it wasn't a - a very posh school and - there wasn't much time to spend on - anything else but just giving you the three R's. I m
ean there was usually forty or fifty in a class and - as I say - the different types.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 You mentioned ex seven before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Standard seven was the highest standard and ex seven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 There was always an ex-seven and usually that was what the
y called the scholarship class. The headmaster took that as distinct from any of the other teachers. Yes, he did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you sit in the same class as standard seven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh no, we - we were - what we done, we were in two rows behind and this headm
aster would give you work to do and he - he himself looked after that. Usually they sat for the exam - for the scholarships which in those days - were only two. Junior City and Free Place. Now then if you got a free place scholarship well it was out of th
e question following it though because it meant you have to - your parents have to buy the books and different things which ran somewhere about twenty pound to start off with which - was prohibitive in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 In our school we used to be sitting in the back row.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 And I used to take some classes and also take some boys to the baths.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 And ring the bell and fill the ink wells - in fact you did no more work after the age of twelve,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well no, you don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did they cane the girls as well as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Ah well now - yes - yes, they did. 'Course I was only with girls in the infants, I was never with girls after but - I w
as in what they call the big boys.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What did you get the cane for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Anything or everything. There was no excuse really, I think they were cane happy. in those days and each teacher used the cane, it wasn't just like today but - cane happy they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Very much so, my father did yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did they ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes, my father was very keen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did they visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did the other children\'85\'85?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 That kind of thing wasn't - done you know in those days. In fact, usually if - if a teacher seen a parent coming they got}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3292730\charrsid483827  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 out the door, they knew there was trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well they did, there were occasions where there was one or two like we had - who were butchers you see and they were - t
hey always contributed quite a lot to the - there was school money in those days you know. You took it on Monday mornings - always took school money - those that could afford it. It'd be coppers - pennies of some, tuppence well like of these see this butc
h
er's family, the Shaws they were - they could give considerably more and so when they had these different collections for different things they of course always came forward for something big. There were one or two families like that who were very well - 
in with the teachers. Incidentally with the clergy too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes, there were - there was cliques - definitely cliques.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How would they be left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Well usually they were the types that were - what I call introverts. The introverts were usually out of things. Whether they chose to be I wouldn't know now. Or whether they were kept out - I think they chose to be cut, you 
know but - the introverts which were quite a few usually, they were the ones that were cut of the gangs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you go to another school afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Only night school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How old were you when you left school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Just on thirteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Would you have stayed longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh yes. In retrospect. I did voluntary go to night}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3292730\charrsid483827  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 school though afterwards myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Why did you leave at thirteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well - economic necessity.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 They gave you an exemption?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh ye
s, you had to pass an exam at St Thomas Street. Yes, you - you applied to leave and you went down to Education Committee offices St Thomas Street, they gave you a paper and - this was during the war of course - and - they also looked into your circumstanc
e
s and then you got a - permission to leave. But - as I say, I was already working strangely enough you know, I was taking milk cut when I was nine. Well then it was necessary for me to find work, I mean things weren't good. I mean, during the war as you k
now prices were high and - money wasn't very high. Father was a dock labourer at the time and they weren't getting a great deal of money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well yes, obviously I must have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 While you were at school did you have a part time job or any means of earning a little regular money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How did you get it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh - went looking for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 You got it yourself did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 O
h yes, in those days it was a great thing in fact - you - you boasted of having a - an every night and Saturday job. You were looked down on if you didn't have this kind of job by other fellows in the school. It was something to have got this job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What exactly did you have to do in this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well I - the first job I had was only nine - took milk out in cans of morning for a little dairy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Every morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Every morning. Seven o'clock. Sunday included. And evenings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What were the hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well I - go in about seven o'clock 'til about half eight and then in the evenings from about four 'til half five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you have any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh good God no. And then later on - later on I - I passed that job over to a sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How much did you get paid for that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Nine}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3292730\charrsid483827  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
pence a week. Nine}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3292730\charrsid483827  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 pence a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you think it was a fair wage or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well I definitely don't think it was a fair wage. But the period - at the period it was - reasonable. Then - then I pas
sed this job over to my sister and I went - every night and Saturday take - delivering groc - greengroceries and fruit for a fruiterer in Oak - Road. And for that I received one and sixpence and a bag of fruit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How long did you work on that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Well I worked on that job every night from four - after leaving school - four 'til about six bar Wednesday, and on Saturday you'd start at nine in the morning go home at one and go back at three and work 'til eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 And you got how much a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 One and six and a bag of fruit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you have any holidays with pay at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No. Now then, I left there to go and take coal out. For a coal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3292730\charrsid483827  }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 merchant who'd gone - been called up for the forces and his sister was running - keeping the business goin
g and I and another chap took coal out in half hundredweights on a hand cart. And we were in the money on that job. I got four shilling a week for that. In the money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Worked - I'll tell you the hours of that - we worked 
- dinner time from school, when we come off school 'til one o'clock, an hour taking it round. At night from four 'til about six and all day Saturday 'til about five Saturday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 And you got four bob?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Got four shillings a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How did you get on with the other people you worked with in all these jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh very well I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How did your employer treat you in all these jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 As an employer to a worker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you like him, how did you feel about him or them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 I don't
 think I had any particular feelings - I just - I was - well I mean a child, I realized - I thought I had to obey them and I had to do it, that's all, I don't think I had any particular feelings against them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How did you feel about the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 I didn't like - that type of work, no. No. I was always had a feeling to do something with me hands I don't know why but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did these jobs you were doing alter you attitude to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 I'd like to ask you about your first full time job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What was that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
First full time job was - against my own inclinations. I went down to the Education Committee officer and he sent me to an office job, he thought I was the clerical type.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 This is when you were thirteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes,
 he sent me to - a Shell factory - a National Shell factory in Edge Lane. In the office. I was an office boy and - they thought that was my -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What did you have to do in that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 The normal office boy's work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What were the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well the - the hours were very long. They were from seven o'clock in the morning 'til five at night. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you work on Sundays or Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Saturday afternoon we had to work but they give us overtime for it. But the money was ten shilling a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you have any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No, I didn't get any holidays there at all, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you feel that ten bob was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well at that time, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you give any of the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 All of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What about the money you received from the other jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 All the money went in the - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What was it spent on then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well on - on keeping us of course. We - I - I got a tanner out of it probably or something like that you know. You get a little h
and back but - you didn't think that you were entitled to any of it somehow. I mean, your mind was that way that you - like contributing to something that - you should be contributing to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How did you get on with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh very well, yes, very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How did the boss treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How did you feel about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well - we didn't have a lot}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3292730\charrsid483827  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3292730\charrsid483827  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
do with us. You know, in an office, as an office boy strangely enough, you - your bosses are all the other staff. The actual boss himself doesn't bother with you. Or he didn't at that time, you were kind of - factotum, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How did you feel about the work - did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 I disliked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did that job alter your attitude to school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No. No, I wouldn't say altered attitude to school, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What about your second job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Now then I left - when the war was over, 1918, Armistice was signed, I went down to the labour again at the education office.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Because you got the sack at the other place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
We didn't, but we got told to try and find other employment you see, we didn't get finished right away. Anyhow I go down and - there was a man there, I just can't recall his name now but he was very keen on me becoming - or go
ing to - be a compositor. And - he tried to talk me into it - in a way I'm sorry I didn't now. He thought I was the type that would be very good for - compositor. And I said, no. I was very keen on engineering - I wanted an engineers apprentice. Very, ver
y keen on engineering. And they sent me to the gas company, Duke Street - workshops.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 It wasn't your father who got you into a trade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh no. No. Me own - he wanted - he wanted me to have a trade. Oh they always wanted me to have a trade but no I g
ot the jobs myself, each one. Nobody really helped - only the Education Officer. Yes. That's right. He sent me up there to be interviewed. I went up to see the works manager there, I was taken on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 As an apprentice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Apprentice engineer - in the p
ress shop. They made their own pressed tools there you know for meter making and that. And - that's where I served me time there, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What hours were they then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Eight o'clock in the morning 'til six at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What about Sundays, Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 And from Saturday - from eight o'clock 'til half twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you work Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you have holidays with pay in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What was your wages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 I started eighteen and nine}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3292730\charrsid483827  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 pence a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you feel that was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
That was a very good wage for an apprenticeship at that time. It was very, very good. Later on it - they dropped back considerably but don't forget this was 1918. The engineers wages at that time incidentally was five pound two and six a week. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 They dropped down to fifty shillings didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 They dropped down to about -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Forty-eight shillings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes. What they were then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you give all this money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 All went - oh yes. That was - in fact that was working class practice them days. You just handed your money over to your mother you know.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Together with the pay check?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes. That was - that was it like, that was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh - well at that tim
e of course the employer treated you as a worker, there wasn't that same - collaboration and cooperation that you're getting today. You were strictly a worker and a servant. That's how you were treated.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 How did you feel about the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 I liked t
he work very good, yes, I didn't like all of the conditions. Toilets and such like were out in the open with - no covering of any kind and - oh yes. Iron - just an iron shed, you know what I mean, this cast iron business like you get down on the Dock Road
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did the job alter your attitude to school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No, if anything I started to go to night school then, that's when I started going. Yes, started going to the technical side then, yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 You stayed there some considerable time did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 I did, I stayed for twenty-seven years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What jobs have you had since then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well since then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What made you leave there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well I'll tell you why. When the - prior to becoming Nationalized then general manager decided to get rid of all 
the ancillaries so that when it was nationalized there was only gas making taken over. Got rid of all the craftsmen, all meter making, all the brass finishers, brass shops, all the fitters - the lot. All the gas fitters even had to be hired to fit the gas
 - cooker. They had all their own in those days but he banished - he cleared the lot. By the time the nationalisation took place was only the bare gas making. Everything else was gone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 That's the reason you left there is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What job have you done since then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Well - then I went down - I was working down on the Dock Road at Harlands for a while. And then I opened - when the war - just after the war this was, 1941, I opened the - with another bloke I opened a greengrocers shop in Mal
lineux Road. Yes. And then I opened another one in High Park - we had two. And we were doing reasonably well. Until - the advent of all the barrow boys. Outside your shop. Well it got that way you - it wasn't a decent living in it. So - then I - I went up
 to Crawfords and - as a matter of fact I wen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3292730\charrsid483827 t to two jobs - that was - I tos}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
sed up, either going to Belmont Road hospital or to Crawfords. You know what settled it? Well - Belmont Road hospital was six pound ten a week, Crawfords was six pound twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you belong to a trade union or professional organisation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Oh yes. Yes. I belonged originally to the A.S.E. - Amalgamated Society of Engineers. And then - that was when I first started serving me time, the men I worked - served me time with was v
ery - keen that I must be a trade unionist. And then it amalgamated and became the forty seven unions went together the A.E.U.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you take part in any of its activities?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh yes. I was branch president for a number of years and I was branch secretary. Also trustee - branch trustee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Do you feel that employers and workers had the same interests or different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Could you explain that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well - it's obvious. The - the were on two different side. If - the employer could c
ut out a worker to make more profit he will do - obviously. Well the worker must try and make the job that - he won't be put out of work, obviously that's not in the bosses interest - that - that's just it. It's economic necessity that if the worker if he
 
- I have had occasions when I worked down on the dock where you be taken on for one particular job. And you knew when that job was finished that you would be out of work. Well obviously you would hold that job back. Now that is - the boss wouldn't look at
 it that way - the employer wouldn't - so obviously you must be - looking at the job - must be two different angles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you feel there was a division of interest amongst the workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh yes, there - there's a lot of divisions, not one division -
 lots of divisions among workers. There are some workers you know who - permanently spend their time carrying favour with the employers, for no other reason that just for their own - aggrandisement, I don't know why. It eventually doesn't do them any good
 
because they - he wash his hands of them just the same as anybody but there's always the other man who does believe he's doing a good days work and that's all he - he - he things of, that he's doing a good day's work and he expects to get a good day's pay
 and a good return for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Some people say that in those days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers - did you feel that or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh yes, there was. In my young days definitely there was. There was a very, very big division.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Oh well - yes, it did really - it must do. Because full time work means that most of your waking hours are spent at work. Therefore it must - make a difference to your life. 'Cos that is really your life. Most of your waking hours are working hours.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you continue to live at home after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 I did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did it make much difference to you - you were thirteen when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well - which way - which way do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No, not in any - not in - couldn't really because - it was the same. I got up at the same time of morning as I always did - 
I was always up early, got out, going to work. No, I don't think it made any difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 With your relationship with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No I don't think so. Not that I - I could recollect. I don't think there could be any marked difference or I would recollect it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 When I left school I though I was a bit better than the lads that were still at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well - I don't say that I - don't forget, I started work during a war. So I mean it had a different - aspect I suppose and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you spend your Sunday any different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you still go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Still went to church. Yes, still went to church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well Sunday evening more than Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 You told me earlier how you spent your spare time, did you spend your spare time any differently after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Well of course there was three nights a week at night school. Oh yes. Monday, Tuesdays and Thursdays I went to night school once I started work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What else did you do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well of course there was quite a lot of homework to be done from these three nights. I usually did that Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What did you do on the other nights?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well the other nights was usually out with the lads. Knocking around the corners I suppose and - down the park kicking a ball about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you ever do any cycling or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Yes, we did a - we - had old bikes, cost a few bob, I think mine cost twelve and six. We used to cycle out of course - the country was pretty near us you know those days. Not as far as it is today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you have any hobbies in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
No, barring as I say the - the cigarette card business, that dropped out during the war. They stopped having cigarette cards but otherwise no - there was no distinct hobby as such.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you go out in the evenings - you told me three evenings already?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 That's right, at night school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you go anywhere else at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Not anywhere as such. We might go down to the Pier}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12934652\charrsid483827  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 head. We used to call going down to the stick - the stick and parade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Who did you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Usually to or three mates.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 The parade - you mean the Ham and b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12934652\charrsid483827 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 g Para}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12934652\charrsid483827 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 e?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes, oh aye, yes, over the water, yes. And - there was no such - no places to go to as such. 
We might go to a picture on a Saturday - a Saturday night - pictures. That would cost you about four}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12934652\charrsid483827  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 pence or five}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12934652\charrsid483827  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 pence. On Saturday night. Other times you might congregate in - in - herb shops as they were - quite a number of herb shops in those days. Qu
ite a number of herb shops - congregate in there you know, you get a - a tuppenny drink and you stay there all the evening with a crowd. They were great places for congregating. They've all closed down - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you ever go to billiard balls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No. No, I didn't go in - there wasn't a lot of billiard balls about at that time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 They opened up more after the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 That's right. Yes. I remember them open after the war - not at that particular time, no. The most billiards were being played th
en in the Catholic clubs - the C.Y.M.S's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you ever go in those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Yes. I went in the C.Y.M.S. later on. I joined the C.Y.M.S. They had quite a considerable - billiard league you know, it was quite a big thing - quite for or five divisions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you still go to church - when did you finish going to church regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well I should say after the war. I came up a bit militant in the different organisations and of course church was out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you make any new friends between leaving school and the end of 1918? Any boys or girls at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh yes, boys, yes. Ones I worked with. Yes, at Edge Lane, yes. There was a couple I made friends with and we knocked about together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you meet them at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 We met them at work - 
I met them at work and we - we got rather interested in photography between us. Yes. There was an - an old hap who was the official photographer up at this munitions works and we got very friendly with him and we took an interest in photography - we bough
t an old box camera and there were plates then, there weren't films and - we did a bit of dabbling as far as our money'd let us in that, and he developed and printed a lot for us - this old chap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you ever bring your friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh yes. Lads - friends, yes, I always brought them home, we used to have quite a few at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you have any special friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No, not special. Only the usual crowd. It was a crowd, you understand me? ; There's probably five, six or seven of them together you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did your parents meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes. They came to the house - the boys came to the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did they expect to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Oh yes. Yes, very much so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you have to be home at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes, usually by ten o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 When was this restriction lifted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Well - more or less after I'd - finished serving me time and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 That was well after 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 It was well after 1918 - about - yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 It Looked as if your parents were very very strict as far as learning a trade was concerned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Father was, yes, very very keen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Have you any idea why that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Yes. Because, as I say, there was a terrific division of - class amongst the workers at that time with the 
tradesmen and the non-tradesmen. And my father was determined that - we were to have a trade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you all have trades then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Both sons, yes. Oh yes. Both lads had trades, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 We didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No, no, but he was very determined over this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you take an interest in politics at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Did you have any political knowledge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 Only what I'd - bibed from the different people that visited me father. That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 So you couldn't say you were politically conscious up to the age of seventeen or eighteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
I was politically conscious, yes. I - I realized there was a lot of injustice if you understand me. I realized that and I - as a matter of fact - I had occasion - I was always looked upon, even among the lads 
at work, as the leader for anything that wanted doing. Was one occasion when we were - we - we reckoned we were being done out of a - a penny a week. In our money and - I went in about this as the spokesman for the other - the other apprentices and the wo
r
ks manager claimed that it was difficult to work this penny in. So I suggested he made it to tuppence then it would be easier. Instead of doing us out of a penny. Anyway we got away with - that was the kind of thing that happened. I was, yes, politically 
- conscious even at that time of injustice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1523865 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 What was your idea of injustice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9062157 JS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9320372\charrsid483827 
Well - injustice - I hated injustice. Even to somebody else - not only to myself - I still do, I'm very, very violent over and injustice to anybody. I react very very vi
olently to it. Don't like it - I don't like to hear of it. I think injustice is a terrific thing.
